##############################
#                            #
#         NINA API           #
#                            #
##############################

------------------------------

* For GNU/LINUX or UNIX users

- Install cmake packages (http://www.cmake.org)
- Build NINA sources with one of the following methods :

  . Using "cmake"

1. cd build/
2. cmake . -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE:STRING=Release
3. make

  . Using "ccmake"
	
1. cd build/
2. ccmake .
3. Then press 'c', update CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE with 'enter' to "Release"
4. Press 'c' again, then press 'g'
5. make

------------------------------

* For Win32 users

- Install cmake packages (http://www.cmake.org)
- Open Cmake.exe and fill the 'source code' and 'binaries building' fields with the path of NINA /build directory
- Click on configure then fill the field CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE with "Release"
- Finish by clicking on generate
- From Visual studio, select the .sln generated into /build and compile the project

------------------------------

NINA library will be built into /lib/Release folder

##############################
#                            #
#         NINA DOC           #
#                            #
##############################

The documentation will be generated under the folder "doc/api-doc"
The NINA project tree is explained into the README file, please refer to it if you are in doubt.

------------------------------

* For GNU/LINUX or UNIX users

- Install doxygen (http://www.doxygen.org)
- cd /build
- make doc

------------------------------

* For Win32 users

- Install doxygen (http://www.doxygen.org)
- From Visual studio, select the .sln generated into /build and run the "doc" target

------------------------------
